column4: Focuses on the importance of the Chinese team (e.g. “We can’t do this without you” or "we need your men to complete the mission")
column6: shows willingness to work together (i.e. implies you are not just using their men) (e.g. "I'm sure we can work this out together")
column8: appeals to officer’s empathy (e.g. “Think about the refugees”)

column3: Dialogue
All we need are men. We have enough supplies for a group of your people to join us. All Iâ€™m asking for is a few of your men.

I speak for both of us when I say we donâ€™t want this to go higher up the command chain. Iâ€™d have to tell my superiors, and scarp my plan. Letâ€™s try to work something out between us, at our level, and prevent those issues.
This is imperative. There are people who need those supplies and without your help that is not going to happen. There must be something we can do to work this out.
I donâ€™t understand why you wonâ€™t help. We have the supplies, you have the men. We need your men.
I just need a few of your men for a short while, and I know you have them to spare.

I can't get my job done without your help. Otherwise I have to notify my commander that we can't follow the plan. I know both of us don't want that to happen - is there a compromise that works for you and me?
We need to get these supplies to those refugees who are suffering, and that can't happen without your men. What can we do to get that done?
We're too few and too busy to do the work alone. We need the help of your men to move and deliver these supplies.
Your army is vast, can you help provide some men for our team? We are well stocked with supplies, but have few men.

There is no way we can move forward without your help. I'd need to cancel our plan and notify my commander, and I don't think either of us wants it to get to that level, so can we sort this out now? There must be a way we can both benefit.
This is a critical mission, as there are refugees that need supplies and without the aid of your men we can't deliver them. Isn't there something we can do to make this work?
I don't believe this. We have ample supplies, but need your men to help. We can't do this without your help since we're already stretched so thin.
It is critically important to both of us that we succeed at this mission. We've got the supplies, we just need a few of your men, and I know they're available. How many can we have?

I feel like this is something we can work out on our level, don't you? If it bumps up to the commander level, we'll have to start all over again, wasting both of our time. Talk to me about what you can do.
We both know the refugee situation is dire. If we can't work together, there will be dire consequences. What do you think is the best way to solve this problem?

Just to reiterate, we've got the supplies handled on our side, so your side just needs to spare a few men to help move the supplies to the refugees. I checked, and you have about 25 men available, just need your OK to assign them.
We have all the supplies necessary and I am aware you have the men I need. We just need more manpower. Please spare a few men to help us with this mission.

We are unable to do this without the extra men. I will have to quit the mission and inform my commander and I think neither of us would want that. Can we please try to make a compromise so we can figure this out on our own, without escalating.
We have no option but to complete this mission, there are people out there that need our help and the supplies we have. We cannot do this without your help. Is there no way for us to work this out?
What? We have all the necessary supplies and we desperately need the extra manpower from your men. We cannot do this without you because we have exerted all other options and have no lieneance.
I do have men available but we are still waiting on supplies from the Chinese team. I need help ensuring that the planes arrive first.
I can support you with manpower if you can make sure that those planes arrive immediately. Otherwise, we cannot work together.
I know that you have connections that can speed up the arrival of the planes. My men are yours if those supplies land soon.
Trust me, I want to help. We need to do this together.
We have the supplies, and I know you have the men. Can't you spare a few of them? What we need is manpower.
There's gotta be something you and I can do. I can't do this alone, and I don't want to notify a higher up. Come on.
We have to work this out. There are refugees that need us, and we can't help them without your men.
What are you taking about? We need men, not supplies.
Would you be able to spare some men? We have plenty of supplies, we just lack hands.
Is there some agreement we can reach? We cannot do the mission without you, and I would prefer to work something out together.
There are many people in need. We have the supplies but not enough manpower to deliver them. Is there any way you can lend us some help?
We have no shortage of supplies, just men. Can you please help us distribute them?
Can you spare a few of your men to help us? We have all of the supplies, we just need men to help us move them.
We can't do this without your men. I don't want to have to notify my commander. It won't end well for either of us. Can we work this out amongst ourselves?
Those refugees need these supplies. This mission has to happen and it can't happen without your men. Is there nothing we can do to work this out?
We have enough supplies but we don't have enough men. That's why we need your men to help us.

We have all the supplies we need to start our joint mission. We just need the manpower to set up security of the site and man the aide station. I know that between our two teams we have enough men to do the job. Let's work together to divide up the existing troops to get the job done.

We need to figure out a compromise together before we involve our commanders. They are depending on us to work together to get this job done and expect us to handle the details and offer them positive solutions rather than problems. We don't want to report what we cannot do but only what we CAN do through mutual cooperation.
Failure to complete the mission of delivering these supplies to the refugees is not an option. We must work together to figure out how best to accomplish this in spite of potential roadblocks.

I am not worried about the delayed supplies for now. We already have plenty of supplies on site to begin the mission. We just need to decide how best to utilize and organize our men to get started until the delayed supplies and troops arrive.
I know you have men free, could you please allow some to help us? We need manpower to distribute the supplies.
We cannot do this alone. i will have to give up the plan and speak to my commander. I don't want us to have to do that; surely we can work something out.
This mission must occur, we must help the refugees. Let's fix this.
We have more than enough supplies, we just need more men as we do not have enough.
Would it be possible for your to spare a few of your available men to help us out? All of the necessary supplies are available, we just need coverage to expedite the plan.

We really need you in order to complete this plan. Otherwise, we will need to send notice to the commander that we are throwing out the plan altogether. Since neither of us want it to come to that, isn't there a compromise that we can reach in this matter?
There has to be something that we can do to work this out. We all really need this mission to happen. These refugees without supplies cannot be served if your men don't help us deliver them.
I beg your pardon? We are already needing more men to assist in this matter. So, if you don't send some of your men to help, then we won't be able to do this at all.
We need more manpower, and I know you have extra men, can you spare some?
I don't want to have to scrap this plan and notify my commander. Im sure we can reach a compromise.
We have to get these supplies to those refugees. There has to be a way to work this out.
We have plenty of supplies but not the manpower. We are stretched so thin. We need your help.
Look, I'm aware you have available men so can't you spare a few to help us out? Supplies aren't an issue, we have plenty but not enough manpower.

The fact is we cannot do it without you. There must be some type of compromise that we can agree on. Otherwise I need to trash the current plan and contact my commander, which isn't something either of us want to happen.
There must be something we can do to work this out. The mission must happen reguardless because refuges need those supplies, but without your men they won't get them.
I don't get it. We have all the supplies, we only need the manpower from you to deliver them. Our team is already thinned out enough, it's impossible without your help.
We have supplies but need help with manpower. Can you spare a few men I know you have a available to help us?

There has to be a compromise we can reach because we cannot do this without you. I'll have to scrap the plan and notify my commander. I know we both don't want it to get to that level so what can we do to figure this out on our level?
Refugees are depending on us to bring them supplies. We need your men to make this delivery happen. What can we do to work this out?
We need more of your men to help us because we are stretched so thin already. We have plenty of supplies, but we can't do this without you.
Can you spare a few of your available men to help us with our manpower needs? We already have the supplies we need for now.
Your assistance is required for our plan to succeed. We need to reach a compromise so that we do not have to cancel.
Refugees must receive these supplies, but we must have the manpower to deliver them. How can we resolve this?
As I already said, we already have the supplies at the moment. We just need the manpower to deliver.
We have supplies for the near term, I know you have men available, can you spare a few to help?
There has to be some compromise, as I cannot do this without you. I would like to avoid scrapping my plan and notifying my commander, can we figure out something on our level?
How can we work this out? There are refugees that need supplies, this mission has to happen and I need your men to deliver them.
We need your men to help, we have enough supplies, we cannot do it without you as we are stretched thin.
we have all the supplies for the near term, we just need manpower, can you spare a few of the available ones to help us?
we can reach a compromise at our level because i am sure we both want to keep this from getting to the commander, we can not do this without you.
is there something we can do to work this out because this mission must happen and we need your men to deliver these supplies to the refugees.
we have plenty of supplies and we need your men to help us as we are stretched so thin and can't do it alone.
We have all the supplies necessary but we just need a few of your men for some extra manpower.
This cannot be completed without your aid. I don't think either of us want me to have to trash this plan and have to go tell me commander, so perhaps we can compromise?
There is absolutely no way for this to work for both of us? Those refugees desperately need these supplies and they will not receive them without the aid of you and your men.
We already have plenty of the needed supplies, we simply need some assistance from your men and we need your men since our men are already being used elsewhere.
I am aware that you have men available and we have all of the supplies but we are in need of manpower. Can you spare a few of them to help us?
Without you, we cannot do this. I'll have to change my plan and notify my commander. I know that we both have the same goals and we should be able to figure this out and compromise.
Without your men, there are refugees that won't receive these supplies. Isn't there something we can work out to make this mission a success?
We are really stretched thin here and we have all of the supplies needed, but we just need your men. Without them, we won't be able to do this.
Listen-we're all set with supplies, but we can't complete this wiyhout more manpower. So could you please spare just a few of your extra men?
There has to be something we can do to compromise. Otherwise I'll have to notify my commander because we'll have to scrap the mission. And I'm pretty sure neither of us wants that to happen.
Are you sure there's nothing we can do? Without manpower we can't deliver these supplies to the refugees.
Huh? We have the supplies, but we're spread so think we just don't have the necessary manpower.
Would it be possible for us to use some of your men? We are good on supplies, but short on manpower.

I'm afraid that will not be acceptable - we need you to move forward. I don't want to have to tell my commander that the mission is canceled, and neither do you. There must be something we can do to come to an agreement.
There are refugees in need of these supplies, and without your help we won't have enough men for delivery. This mission is essential - is there any way we can figure this out?
Huh? Like I said, we only need men, not more supplies. We can't complete the mission without your help.
People are waiting to be of assistance
There might not be enough to make a didfference
Their job was to protect the base
We need more equipment to finish the job
I realize that you have men available, so can you lend us a few? We are need of more men to assist us.
It will be necessary to collaborate to avoid scrapping the mission. Surely together we can arrive at a solution.
Given the need, we must carry out the mission. Surely we can work together and salvage it.
We have the supplies, but we will need your men to assist us as we have a dearth of manpower.
Can you leave us some of your men available to help us? we have supplies for the short term but we need help with jobs
I know we can solve the fault in our level, but without you we can not do it, I will discard my plan and I will let my commander know, we have a commitment to discover and reach
There are many refugees who need our supplies, therefore we must complete this mission, but we need the help of their men, there must be something to do to solve it
We need your men to help us to deliver the supplies, we need all the help possible, personal lack and we can not do it without you

If you cannot help, my commander will be told that we have to come up with a new plan. You are integral to the plan. If we can talk it out we can come to an understanding.
How can we make this work? One way or another, we have got to complete this task. Refugees are waiting for these supplies and we can't do it without your help.
I don't understand, your lack of supplies doesn't matter. We have supplies, we only need your men. They are important to the mission, we have done everything we can.
We have the supplies needed, we just need a few of your men to help us.
There must be something we can do. I will have to report this to my commander if this doesn't work out, and I know that isn't desirable for either of us.
We need your men to help get these supplies to refugees, are there no other options?
But we have the supplies needed and we cannot complete this mission without your men.
We have plenty of supplies, but we need more man power. Can you please send more of your men?
Is there anyway we can come to an agreement? I'd really hate to cancel my plans and take this up with our higher commanders. We need your help.
Many refugees need our supplies and we need your men to help deliver them. Can we try working this out?
We have enough supplies and we really need your help. We can't do this without your help.
I can see that you've got all the men you need. We only need some additional manpower, so would it be possible for some of them to help us out?

We will have to reach some kind of agreement because if I have to drop my current plan then I have to elevate this and call my superiors because I can't get this done otherwise. It would look better if we worked it out ourselves.
If I had your men then I could deliver the supplies to the refugees. We have to reach some sort of compromise because this mission has to be accomplished successfully.
Why would you say that? You have the men. We have the supplies. If you put those together then we can do it. Otherwise, we are already struggling.
All I am asking for is a bit of extra manpower, no supplies. Please help us by providing a few extra men.
How about we keep this from moving higher up the chain and reach a compromise right now. I think that would be easier for everybody, right?
You must see that it is imperative that these refugees receive the supplies. Is there someway we can work out an agreement for some of your men to help us?
You need to understand that I am not asking for any supplies. What I am asking for, is men. We are stretched too thin right now to provide all the manpower.

How? We have lots of supplies. All we need is your men to help us
May you give us a couple of your men who are available to aid us? We need the strength of these men and have the included supplies for the near term.

Without you, we can't do this. I'll notify the commander after throwing away my plan. Let's try to figure it out together so we can all understand and be cohesive. We have to be able to agree on something.
We need men to deliver these supplies to the refugees so we cannot fail this mission. Are there any available options that will work?
How? Lend us some of your men to aid us because we have all these supplies and cannot do this alone as we are already depleted.
Would you kindly spare some of your men to help us. We have a shortage of manpower despite having all the needed supplies
Unfortunately given the circumstances and urgency I was hoping we can do this at our level without necessarily involving the chain of command.
This mission is really paramount as they are some refugees who need the supplies urgently, do you we can work something out?
The supplies are quite a lot and our man will not be able to supply them alone, we really need your help
Could you spare you available men, we need more help. We have all the supplies they need.
We need you help. We don't want to have to tell the commander about this so can we handle it on our level?
Can you please help, the mission is important. There are refugees in need and we could use your help.
We are low on help. We have supplies, we just need more people.
Would you still be able to assist us with those men you have? We have the supplies, but need the physical support.
We need your assistance in this and would like to compromise. I'll notify the commander and we'll try to find a plan that will work for both of us.
We need to support and assist the refugees and your soldiers are the only way to deliver the supplies. How can we make this work?
Please reconsider - all of the supplies are here, we just need the manpower as we're are thinly stretched.
Our team has supplies, but we need men. Do you have a few free men to spare?
Your help is vital. If I can't achieve my plan, I'll have to tell my commander about your unwillingness to help. Neither of us want that, so I think there has to be some agreement we can come to.
Refugees need these supplies, and we can't get it to them without your men. This mission is vital. There has to be way we make this work.
If we had enough men, we wouldn't ask for your help, but we don't. All we need is some men, we already have the necessary supplies.
You have the men there to help. Even if you only send a few it would assist us greatly. We have everything we need except the men to preform.
We are not able to complete our mission without your men to aid us. I dont wont to go over your head but if forced I will. Could we not come to an agreement that will let us both succeed?
There is no other option, we must complete our mission or the refugees will suffer. We cant give them their supplies without your manpower. how can we make this happen?
NO! We have all the supplies already we just need your men to help deliver them with the men that we already have.
Can you spare a few of your available men to help us? We already have the supplies, but we need manpower.
I'll have to scrap my plan and notify my commander if you don't lend a hand. Neither of us want it to get to that level so we should try and figure out a compromise between us.
We have to work out how to complete this mission. The refugees need these supplies and we need your men to deliver them.
What do you mean? We have plenty of supplies, but we need your men to help us. We're stretched thin already so we can't do it without you.
I know you've got men, can you spare just a few of them to help us? We all have short - term supplies, we just need manpower.

But without you, we can't. I'm going to scrap my plan and let my commander know, I think we both want to keep it from reaching that level so we can try to figure out something at our level? We have to reach a compromise.
This mission must take place, there are refugees who need this supply and we can not deliver it without your men. Can't we do anything to work this out?
What? But we have plenty of supplies, we need your men to help us, we can't do it without you since we are stretched so thin already.
We need more manpower, could you spare more men. I know you have extra men, could you spare just a few?
If you don't help I will have to scrub the mission and notify my commander. Before it gets to that point we should work something out. Lets make a deal.
This needs to work, these people need their supplies. We cannot deliver them without your men. How can we get this mission accomplished?
We are spread really thin, we have supplies we need men. We need your help.
can you just spare a few of them to help us I know you have men available need manpower.
scrap my plan and notify my commander,we both would like to keep it from getting to level so can we try and figure something out.
there are refugees that need these supplies and without your men we can't deliver them. Is there nothing we can do to work this out?This mission has to happen,
we have plenty of supplies, we need your men to help us. can't do it without you since we are stretched so thin
I am aware that you have men available, could a few of them come help us? We have the supplies for the near term, but we need more manpower.

We can't do this without you. I'll have to scrap my plans and notify my commander. I think we should both keep it from getting to that level, so lets work something out between the two of us. There has to be a way we can compromise.
This mission is vital. There are refugees who need the supplies, and without your men they can't be delivered. Is there nothing we can do to make this work?
What? We have plenty of supplies, we just need your men to help us. We cannot do it without you, as we are already stretched so thinly.
We have all needed supplies, can you please send additional men to assist?
There is always a solution, especially with team work. What do you need from me to make this plan work?
The only way to assist the refugees and delivery their needed supplies is with your assistance in valuable manpower.
We have all of the supplies needed. The only aspect that is needed from you is manpower. It cannot be done without you and your men.
Would you be willing to spare a few of your men to help us? We have all the supplies for the near term, we just need a few more hands.

This won't be possible without you. I'll have to scrap my plan and notify my commander, and I don't think either of us wants it to get to that point so is it possible to figure something out? I'm sure there's a compromise we can reach.
This mission is of vital importance, we really need your men to deliver supplies to these refugees. There has to be something we can do to work this out?
We have enough supplies, we just need your men to help us, we won't be able to do it without you since we already have a lot going on as is.
We can still complete this mission, we just need some help from your men.
If we compromise, we can still do this together. If we don't this whole thing has to be scrapped, and we both know neither of us want that.
Refugees need these supplies, and they're depending on us to get them. Are you sure we can't work anything out to help them?
The supplies aren't the issue, its the manpower to move them that is. If we work together we can accomplish this.
Will you be able to spare a few men to help us? We already have all the supplies for the near term, we just need manpower.

We really can't do this without your help. I'll have to do away with my plan and notify my commander. I think we both don't want that to happen so can we try to figure something out on our level? We can compromise.
The mission is a must, there are refugees that need these supplies and we need your men to make the delivery happen. Can something work out?
What do you mean? We have plenty of supplies and we just need your men to help us. we really can't do it without you. we are stretched so thin.
We have supplies that I can spare for a few of you men for manpower.
Lets compromise and figure this out on our level since we have to do this together and that way we don"t have to notify our commanders and scrap the plans.

We have plenty of supplies for your men and besides we cannot do it without your help.
I know you have spare men available. Can you allow a few of them to help us move supplies? They are near term and we just need manpower to move them.

Please can you help us out by sparing some men for the work. This will allow us to complete this effort as quickly and effeciently as possible.
Please be courteous of others and please do not get in our way. We need to come to compromise to get this to work.
I am sorry I need to speak to your supervisor to help make a decision. We need the manpower to help out

I do not agree with you not helping out. This is going to make the situation much more difficult. We really need your assistance to get the job done. We are already stretched thin and could really utilize your cooperation in helping out.

I understand your concern about the planes. I would probably feel the same way as you at first. I think we can work as a team here, though. We have some supplies to tie everyone over till the plane comes. No problem. We just need a few more soldiers. Let's help each other out here. What do you say?
Let's work as a team here. My commander will be asking questions, and I think it would be great to have concrete solutions for all of us on how best to carry out this mission

It's important we work together to carry out this mission because the refugees are in dire need of supplies. Let's work as a team here to help. More men are absolutely critical in order to distribute these supplies.

We are here to help the refugees. We have the suppies, but many of them will die if we don't work together as a team to get these supplies to them for their survival. How can we not do everything possible to help them?

I think that we can reach a mutually satisfactory arrangement that will avoid my having to notify my commander and cancel the mission plan.
The refugees are experiencing a crisis right now and time is of the essence. We have the supplies. We just need a little extra manpower that you can provide. What can we do for you to make this work?

We are here to help the refugees. We have the suppies, but many of them will not make it if we don't cooperate as a team to get these supplies to them for their benefit. How can we not do everything possible to help them?

I need your guys for this mission. I don't want to involve the Corporal, so let's just figure this out. We've got to put our heads together.

Man, listen. We've got the supplies. But we need your guys now desperately, because we just don't have the manpower to do it without y'all.

Say WHAT? I can't believe you won't help. We have beaucoup supplies, but without your men we're screwed! We don't have the troops.
like in Korea, your men follow us and pick up the weapons of downed troops
Without some of your men we will surely be outnumbered.
the refugees are dependent on delivery of supplies and your team is crucial to success
we will remember your lack of cooperation. We will continue regardless even though we are greatly stressed.
You have soldiers and we have the supplies so let's work together and get the mission completed.
